## What to look for when choosing an automated order entry system

**Format coverage.** Ask any vendor to process a sample of your actual inbox — not a curated demo dataset. Include your most informal orders. The accuracy on those samples tells you what the tool actually handles.

**Human review design.** Look for confidence scoring on individual line items, not order-level accept/reject. A system that flags specific uncertain items is more useful than one that rejects entire orders for manual re-entry.

**Deployment timeline.** Template-based tools take three to six months because each customer format requires individual configuration. AI-native tools take two to six weeks because format variability is handled by default. The deployment timeline is a signal about the tool's architecture.

**ERP integration specifics.** Confirm which version of your ERP, pre-built connector or custom development, and IT hours required for setup. "We integrate with SAP" needs to be more specific before it means anything.

