## Frequently Asked Questions

**What is automated order entry?**

Automated order entry is software that receives incoming orders and enters them into your ERP without manual data entry. For distribution businesses, the key capability is handling unstructured formats: free-text emails, informal product descriptions, and orders that don't conform to a template. AI-native tools interpret meaning; legacy tools require pre-built templates.

**Can automated order entry handle unstructured email orders?**

AI-native tools can, yes. The system interprets free-text descriptions, informal product references, and "same as last time" requests using account history and semantic catalog matching. Template-based tools cannot handle unstructured emails without a configured template for each customer format.

**How do I eliminate manual data entry in my distribution order desk?**

Capture incoming orders automatically, interpret any format via AI, match products with confidence scoring, route uncertain items to human review, and push confirmed data to your ERP via API. At Meesenburg Romania, this approach achieved 50% full automation and 98% no-modification accuracy on production orders.

**What is the ROI of automated order entry for distributors?**

At 8 minutes per order and 200 orders per day, manual entry consumes approximately 6,700 staff-hours per year. With 80% automation, labor savings alone are typically $130,000 to $160,000 annually. Error cost savings add another $150,000 to $300,000 at a 3% manual error rate. Combined payback periods typically range from three to twelve months.

**How long does it take to implement automated order entry?**

AI-native tools deploy in two to six weeks. Template-based tools take three to six months due to per-customer template configuration requirements. The deployment timeline reflects the tool's architecture: AI handles format variability by default; templates require configuration for each new format.
